main event: A disc-shaped object was observed on radar in Corvallis, Oregon on September 7, 1963.
interesting points: The object was 15 feet in diameter and appeared at an elevation of 45 degrees, traveling in a NE direction at approximately 6000 feet altitude,It was confirmed by visual observation and military control tower checks indicating no planes in the area,The observation lasted for about 3-5 minutes,There was 'noise' on the radar scope which contributed to insufficient data on this observation,The subject of the sighting had security clearance.
witness description: A former Air Force pilot with a master's degree in mechanical engineering and a local dentist.
